<p>The key insight: AEO and GEO both build on SEO fundamentals. Strong <a href="/glossary/on-page-seo/">on-page SEO</a>, solid <a href="/glossary/technical-seo/">technical SEO</a>, and high-quality content are prerequisites for all three strategies.</p>
<h2>How GEO, AEO, and SEO Work Together</h2>
<p>Most marketers make the mistake of treating these as separate strategies with separate budgets. In practice, the overlap is massive.</p>
<h3>The Three-Layer Visibility Model</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="GEO AEO SEO three-layer visibility model showing how each strategy builds on the previous" src="/images/blog/geo-aeo-seo-three-layer-model.webp" /></p>
<p>Think of it as stacking layers, not choosing lanes.</p>
<p><strong>Layer 1: SEO (Foundation)</strong>
Build a technically sound website with strong content and backlinks. This creates the indexed, authoritative content base that both answer engines and AI models rely on.</p>
<p><strong>Layer 2: AEO (Answer Layer)</strong>
Structure your SEO content for direct answer extraction. Add FAQ schema. Use definition-lead sentences. Target <a href="/blog/optimize-people-also-ask/">People Also Ask</a> queries. This turns your ranked content into snippet-winning content.</p>
<p><strong>Layer 3: GEO (Citation Layer)</strong>
Enhance your content with statistics, original data, and cross-platform authority. Allow AI crawlers. Create an llms.txt file. Build entity presence across platforms AI models cross-reference. This turns your authoritative content into AI-cited content.</p>
