<h2>How to Optimize for All Three: Implementation Checklist</h2>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Quick-start implementation checklist for SEO AEO and GEO optimization" src="/images/blog/geo-aeo-seo-implementation-checklist.webp" /></p>
<p>Here is the exact process to optimize content for SEO, AEO, and GEO at the same time.</p>
<h3>Step 1: Build the SEO Foundation</h3>
<p>Every piece of content needs these basics before you think about AEO or GEO:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Target keyword in title, H1, first 100 words, and meta description</li>
<li>[ ] Clear H2/H3 heading hierarchy covering subtopics</li>
<li>[ ] Internal links to related content (3-5 per 1,000 words)</li>
<li>[ ] External links to authoritative sources (2-3 per post)</li>
<li>[ ] Optimized images with descriptive alt text</li>
<li>[ ] Fast page load (under 3 seconds)</li>
<li>[ ] Mobile-responsive design</li>
<li>[ ] <a href="/glossary/xml-sitemap/">XML sitemap</a> submitted to Google Search Console</li>
</ul>
<p>For new websites, start with our <a href="/blog/seo-new-website/">SEO for new websites guide</a>.</p>
<h3>Step 2: Structure Content for Answer Engines</h3>
<p>Once the SEO foundation is solid, add the AEO layer:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Open each major section with a definition-lead sentence</li>
<li>[ ] Add FAQ schema with 4-6 question-answer pairs per post</li>
<li>[ ] Use question-based H2 headings that match PAA queries</li>
<li>[ ] Keep answer paragraphs under 60 words for snippet extraction</li>
<li>[ ] Add HowTo schema for step-by-step content</li>
<li>[ ] Include tables comparing options (answer engines pull these directly)</li>
<li>[ ] Use numbered lists for processes and bulleted lists for features</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 3: Optimize for Generative AI Citation</h3>
<p>Layer in GEO tactics on top of your SEO and AEO work:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Include 3-5 statistics with named sources per 1,000 words</li>
<li>[ ] Build content clusters of 10+ pages around each core topic</li>
<li>[ ] Allow AI crawlers in <code>robots.txt</code> (GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot, Google-Extended)</li>
<li>[ ] Create and maintain an <a href="/blog/llms-txt-guide/">llms.txt file</a></li>
<li>[ ] Publish original research, surveys, or data studies</li>
<li>[ ] Maintain consistent entity information across LinkedIn, Crunchbase, Wikipedia, and industry directories</li>
<li>[ ] Use author bylines with verifiable credentials</li>
<li>[ ] Add speakable structured data for voice-AI compatibility</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 4: Track and Iterate</h3>
<p>Optimization is not a one-time task. Monitor all three channels:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Track keyword rankings weekly (SEO)</li>
<li>[ ] Monitor featured snippet wins and losses (AEO)</li>
<li>[ ] Check AI citation presence monthly using tools like <a href="https://www.perplexity.ai">Perplexity</a> and ChatGPT (GEO)</li>
<li>[ ] Review Google Search Console for AI Overview impressions</li>
<li>[ ] Audit AI crawler access quarterly using server logs</li>
</ul>
<p>For tracking AI visibility specifically, read our guide on <a href="/blog/track-ai-search-visibility/">tracking AI search visibility</a>.</p>
