<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What does GEO stand for in marketing?</strong></p>
<p>GEO stands for Generative Engine Optimization. It is the practice of optimizing content so that AI platforms like ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, and Claude cite or reference it in their generated responses. GEO focuses on topical authority, factual density, and structured formatting.</p>
<p><strong>Is AEO the same as GEO?</strong></p>
<p>AEO and GEO are related but different. AEO (Answer Engine Optimization) targets featured snippets, AI Overviews, and voice assistant responses within search interfaces. GEO (Generative Engine Optimization) targets citations inside standalone AI chat platforms. Some practitioners use the terms interchangeably, but the platforms and tactics differ.</p>
<p><strong>Does GEO replace SEO?</strong></p>
<p>No. GEO builds on SEO fundamentals. AI models rely on the same authority, credibility, and content quality signals that search engines use. Without strong SEO, your content is unlikely to be indexed, linked, or recognized as authoritative enough for AI citation. SEO is the foundation. GEO is an additional layer.</p>
<p><strong>How do I know if AI models are citing my content?</strong></p>
<p>Test by asking specific questions about your industry on ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini. Check whether your brand, data, or content is referenced. Monitor server logs for AI crawler activity (GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot). Track referral traffic from AI platforms in Google Analytics. Read our <a href="/blog/track-ai-search-visibility/">AI search visibility tracking guide</a> for a detailed process.</p>
<p><strong>Which should I prioritize: SEO, AEO, or GEO?</strong></p>
<p>Start with SEO. It is the foundation that both AEO and GEO depend on. Once your site has a technically sound structure, quality content, and growing organic traffic, layer in AEO tactics (structured data, FAQ schema, answer formatting). Then add GEO tactics (AI crawler access, original data, cross-platform authority). Most optimization work serves all three simultaneously.</p>
